<TITLE> International education fair kicks off on Nov 9 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 5 (bdnews24.com) - One of the largest education fairs held in Bangladesh kicks off on Nov 9 when representatives of more than 50 educational institutes from around the world gather at Bashundhara City. The four-day Dhaka International Education Fair for 2007 aims to help students make an informed decision on their options for further education overseas. "About 50 to 60 representatives from foreign educational institutes are taking part in the fair," event organiser Kazi Faridul Haque told bdnews24.com. "Students will be able to select suitable courses as well as register for higher degrees under one platform," added Haque. The fair will offer students advice on what courses are most suitable for them well as suggesting appropriate destinations. Prospective overseas students with appropriate qualifications can interview for admission during the fair. Information on scholarship opportunities and tuition fees will also be available with other important financial advice. Various banks will participate in the event to assist students with educational loans. Representatives from universities and colleges in the UK, USA, Malaysia, China, Australia, Thailand, Japan, Ukraine, Cyprus and India will attend the exhibition. The fair will be inaugurated by advocate Sultana Kamal, executive director of Ain O Shalish Kendra. The fair will remain open for four days from Nov 9, from 10 in the morning until 9 at night. bd
